Still haven't visited? Been a while? Just curious? Get a sneak peek inside our mad science lair!
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.makerbar.com/?attachment_id=376" rel="attachment wp-att-376"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-376" alt="2012-12-19 20.52.46" src="http://blog.makerbar.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/2012-12-19-20.52.46-e1356059189462-1024x171.jpg" width="620" height="103" /></a>Click the panorama to zoom in and get inside a Soldering Wednesday.</p>
The MakerBar is a 1,400 square-foot hideout for makers. We modify and build high-tech stuff for the sheer fun of it, and have built a place where anyone is welcome to join in. Our workshop includes machine tools...

<a href="http://blog.makerbar.com/?attachment_id=377" rel="attachment wp-att-377"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-377" alt="2012-12-16 22.27.53" src="http://blog.makerbar.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/2012-12-16-22.27.53-1024x768.jpg" width="620" height="465" /></a>

&nbsp;

...chests of  hand tools...

<a href="http://blog.makerbar.com/?attachment_id=379" rel="attachment wp-att-379"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-379" alt="2012-10-23 22.07.49" src="http://blog.makerbar.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/2012-10-23-22.07.49-1024x768.jpg" width="620" height="465" /></a>

&nbsp;

...and three 3D printers like this MakerBot Cupcake.

<a href="http://blog.makerbar.com/?attachment_id=381" rel="attachment wp-att-381"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-381" alt="2012-12-16 22.28.33" src="http://blog.makerbar.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/2012-12-16-22.28.33-1024x768.jpg" width="620" height="465" /></a>

&nbsp;

You can browse shelves of electronic components...

<a href="http://blog.makerbar.com/?attachment_id=382" rel="attachment wp-att-382"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-382" alt="2012-12-16 22.27.42" src="http://blog.makerbar.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/2012-12-16-22.27.42-1024x768.jpg" width="620" height="465" /></a>

